caption: Nice restaurant with a cool atmosphere in Old Town. The drink menu is was more interesting than the food one. The appetizers were great - we had the soft veal meatballs and the delicious cauliflower. The entrees were a bit disappointing though - the steak bernaise was boring and the fish and chips oily. Service was awesome though!

Chicagos limitations on restaurants make them uninhabitibal. Sucks for the businesses and staff.  They had window walls open enough to make it feel lile you were sitting outdoors.  Not able to do it at 30 degrees.
Steak frites. Yes yes yes! Thanks for being in my life. Lol. Nice place for a date.
Great food , fantastic service

Food is good, but forgettable.  Service is okay.  Location is fantastic.  Happy is a good value for $5 limited drink menu. Not expecting a Michelin restaurant, but after 4 visits over three years in the neighborhood...  Three Stars.
Great happy hour!

Left my husband standing idly X 10 minutes when he went down to put in an order. No idea why. Possibly because they cater to a younger group? I don’t know. No incentive to return. Feel like 2nd rate patrons at 1st rate prices.
Solid food, hit up the farmers market on the weekend and grab a bite after or vice versa. Won't be disappointed.
Nice place but the they were a little bit disrespectful with us

✅ Delicious food ✅ Friendly staff (shouts out to Carlos!) ✅ ≥ 6ft. table separation with outdoor seating ✅ Surprisingly good music selection  I loved the steak frites, blackened walleye and grilled summer squash. Can't wait to try the rest of their menu 🤤

Greatly curated craft cocktails menu and great recommendations from knowledgeable servers. Dinner was delicious and food was cooked exactly as we had ordered and the 3 people in our party all had great reviews of all food and drinks. We didn't get a chance dessert but next time we are in. LOVE THIS PLACE and their throwback mid-century modern vibe, dimly lit afterglow and I cant say enough about the staff....read more below for a dramatic story..  An amazing staff with the heart of gold, from the manager to the host everyone in this establishment is amazing. I found out the hard way when my wife left her wedding ring on the table of this restaurant and only realized after we had Uber-ed away. We  quickly turned around and looked onto our previous table with horror when we noticed that the table had been stripped of dinnerware, cutlery, and the table cloths.  The entire staff, every single staff member, helped us turn the place upside down after hours in their own time off. They volunteered once their shifts were over since they could see how distraught my wife and I were. Well after almost two hours of sifting through trash and linen hampers we finally found my wives ring. Through tears of joy we thanked everyone who helped  I owe this staff my gratitude and I will not forget any of them for their efforts. Truely touched our hearts and restored faith in humanity
Wine selections are worthy. Food is yummy. Service is friendly and quick. Ambiance is really nice.
The cooking was delicious and my friends were very  glad that we decided to have our dinner from there.
Great staff and food

Was the most amazing place. Great ambiance and even better service and food! Ryan the manager was the best manager we have ever experienced and he went out of if his way to make us feel special. We will recommend this to everyone and we will be back all the time! I would recommend this to everyone!!!!
Great dinner. We had the burger and fish and chips and both were amazing. We also had two appetizers and they were so good. Drinks were awesome and service was great

The astonishing atmosphere is worth every penny, whether dinning in for dinner or a family gathering for brunch. I love the decor and the ambiance makes me feel nostalgic and right at home. The owners Ryan and Dan are always there and are accommodating to their patrons. Derek, the lead mixologist and Sarah their top food server are so professional, I can not be more happy with my experience everytime I pay them a visit. Highly recommended and you will not be let down! Scallops, oysters (east and west coast) and cornbread for dinner is one of their best on the menu and their specials on mimosas are incredibly delicious for your weekend brunch! You can't help but make this your regular go-to restaurant!
really well prepared, delicious food. great beer list. friendly service. check out the patio, weather permitting
Solid
Nice place to have brunch with friends.
Nice place to catch a cocktail and some bites after a day at the zoo or conservatory. Go for good food and solid cocktails. Waitstaff really nice and friendly.
The chicken here was one of the best meals I've had in Chicago!!!
Excellent food and service, great atmosphere. Fish and chips were great.
Nice atmosphere and drinks. But salmon was not fresh enuf. But chocolate chunk cookie was dreamy!
Excellant food, food and prices. Well worth the Fish dinner. Highly recommend.

Really good breakfast! Prompt, friendly service, fresh made food, reasonable prices for a hotel restaurant in Old Town. Also has very good cocktails and bar snacks in the evening. Not a proper "bar", does close at 11 on the weekends.

After waiting about 40 minutes asked if they could send the kids grilled cheese out asap. 30 minutes later were served a completely burned grilled cheese, followed immediately by the adult entrees. Bun on the burger also burned black.
Chicken Sandwich came with two bottom buns and the skin was congealed. Really not good.
A great restaurant in a tremendous location in Old Town, at Wells & Lincoln. Stop in for cocktail and stay for the food and sights.

This is my new favorite place in Lincoln Park! With a few problems of my own involving me not remembering where I parked my car, I stumbled upon it, to my great relief. Wait staff member Emma and night manager Kristen we're great! Emma made me feel like a member of her family, and Kristen found my car. She was an important part my successful evening. Besides that, the food was superb, and so was the wine! They also charged my phone!
Class with fantastic service.!
Good food, great cocktails
Good

The space is pretty good with a nice outdoor area, the burger was decent (though the order was wrong). The coke was flat (which the staff replaced). the spaghetti was cooked al dente but was a starter size. All of this would have been fine had the staff not been so rude, toxic and unengaged. It’s saturday night and a little late and the staff were desperate to go home as if they were in a prison (who were the guards or inmates it’s hard to tell)... we checked before entering if we’d be rushed and assured we wouldn’t be... huh. I think there was one decent waitress but unfortunately she wasn’t ours! the worst service i’ve had in 2 years in the US.
Ummm hard to rate appropriately. Great location, funky place in a good way, menu mildly interesting...not bad, but not great

I am staying at The Hotel Lincoln. I was super tired after exploring yesterday and just wanted to be alone in my room and eat dinner while watching tv. I went downstairs to the Kennison and sat at the bar, which needed a good wipe down yet there were barely any customers present...so it should have been taken care of prior to me sitting down. The bartender stopped his personal conversation with his friend seated at the bar to take my order. I ordered a glass of white wine and put in my to-go order for the Fried Chicken Sandwich. The wine was delish albeit a small pour. I sat rolling my eyes while the bartender and his friend discussed breakup tactics and whether they prefer to be broken up with or if they prefer to be the heartbreaker. I don't think personal conversations like that should happen in front of customers. It is very unprofessional. My order came out very quickly already packed in a brown paper bag with utensils and napkins. I am not going to lie: I was pumped about my sandwich and tv plans. I finished my wine and headed back to my room. I was really disappointed when I opened my food order and noticed that the kimchi slaw that was listed as a side was not included in my takeout container. There were a lot of fries but I was really wanting to try that slaw. The chicken was flavorful but on the greasier side, instead of totally crispy. Based on this experience, I would pick another spot in Lincoln Park even if you are staying at the Hotel Lincoln.

Friday night - accessible due to hotel.  Good service.  I found the menu a little limiting... fish and chips was “ok”, hot and fresh and plentiful, visually appealing. but fish texture was a smidge mushy in spots.  Nice wine selection.  Great service which boosted the 3 stars for food to 4 star overall.  A little pricey?
Great Old Fashion with Hazelnut bitters

Service was good, our server was constantly around, adding water or ready to take care of requests. Food was mediocre, it was a “bar-quality food”, we were expecting a lot more. It was good, but nothing to write home about, very forgettable. Menu is very small (1 page), but it’s not necessarily a bad thing - but in that case one would expect the dishes to be excellent quality with some special flavor/presentation etc to it, and it was not the case. Drinks are overpriced, but it is probably par for the area. The restaurant settings also conveyed the impression of an average place to stop over for casual lunch.

Place is nice and contemporary, with plenty of tables and chairs in a busy part of town - Lincoln Park Zoo is literally across the street, so it's a bit busy to walk around, and parking is almost impossible to find.  The food is tasty, as we had brunch, so the bacon was nicely cooked, egg dishes were nicely made and appearance artful, and drinks well made. It was all a 5 star rating until I saw the bill - mine alone was over 40% of the bill with a party of 10 people. The drinks were most of my costs and it was a simple screwdriver. If I do come next time again, I won't be drinking anything except for 1 drink and water. Night clubs are cheaper on mixed drinks.  Also, our waiter, though he was decent, didn't really come around too much, only to serve us the expensive drinks when they are low in quantity. I didn't like this pre, during and post.  Regardless, it's a nice setting on a Saturday. I think there's valet parking, bathrooms are in the way back somewhere (I had to ask twice), and again, plenty of seating, so the wait time is probably not that bad.  But again, service is iffy and drinks are expensive - next time I'll bring my own. Or just drink water, if they don't charge for that.

(Translated by Google) Place delight! Worth to have breakfast, brunch, lunch, happy hour, dinner ... good too!  (Original) Delícia de lugar! Vale tomar café da manhã, brunch, almoço, happy hour, jantar... bom demais!

Great location! I went for brunch with a friend and the restaurant is really cute. They have great brunch drink deals which I was pleasantly surprised since so many places will change you $10 for a mimosa and here it's $5. I would definitely recommend going here, especially if you're staying at the hotel.
Great drinks
Awesome staff and good food
Good service and well prepared food. Not overly expensive.
Flavors take center stage here. A couple of dishes blended spices so creatively that it knocked us off our feet. One was the cauliflower and one of the pasta dishes.
the rooms are spacious and the food is good

My wife and I went there for dinner. I had the steak frites and my wife had a salad - she liked hers and my dinner was just above average  There are probably better places in the area for a steak but this wasn't bad.  Their Old Fashioned (No. 4) was AMAZING though and I highly recommend it. We both enjoyed our desserts, she had a raspberry butter cake and I had the warm chocolate cookie with ice cream.
Limited menu. Very expensive for the quality

Thanks for your generosity ‘The Kennison’ for hosting the special needs family dinner night.  When establishments take the time, not only to create a welcoming and comfortable environment for special needs individuals, but to host a special event for families with special members, it is really encouraging,  heartwarming and generous.
Burger was outstanding and the best coffee ice cream I have ever had.  Not from Chicago but will be back here if I visit again.

There are lots of great reviews on here and appetizing pics of dishes.  However, my experience at the Kennison this past weekend left more to be desired.  1. The serving staff’s dress was very unprofessional. The manager had on jeans and cowboy boots, the table servers had an assortment of footware from white sneakers, to mountain boots, and there was an obvious theme missing with how they should all look.  2. Our waiter had an extremely poor concept of time. After seating us we waited 20 minutes to order and the space was not full, so he wasn’t overly busy.  It was to the point where we asked another staff member to take our order, but he looked like he was still in high school and told us sorry he couldn’t as he laughed. He would have left it at that had I not suggested he then get out waiter. Upon our waiter finally arriving we felt we needed to order everything at once just to be safe. So, we were then filling his note sheet with scribble.  3. We ordered the beef tar tar and olives to start. Both were good. But the waiter expected me to keep my used beef fork for my main dish. In which I said I’d like a new one. So, I was brought a new one, but my wife did not get the same option. You should not have to ask for a new fork! Especially when you leave/put your used one on the discarded plate.  4.  My wife ordered the steak frites $28. In which if you’ve ever had frites. This came out as a 1 big hunk of ribeye steak. Nothing as expected! With more fat than meat and the fat was not the sort of thing where you could cut around it. It ran throughout the entire steak making it impossible to really eat. So my wife really did not eat.  5. I ordered the double burger, but instead of getting the option to choose how the meat was to be prepared I was told it would be prepared medium. It was not the sort of thing where it was the chef’s recommendation for temp. I was told. So, I was left felling like I had no choice.  6. At the end of the meal I was hoping the manager would make her rounds to our table before our plates were cleared, so my wife could explain how she was not able to cut into her steak (virtually leaving the entire thing in tact) however she did not come until it was time to pay and all she simply did was drop off the check. Not once asked us how everything was.  7. One would think if you leave an 8oz steak on your plate someone should be telling someone and someone should be inquiring to the guest how everything was, but nothing.  With 100’s of options in the city that offer better, more experienced, standardized-professional, and attentative table service. More/higher quality menue options, and overall better quality experience I think we will have to pass on returning to this spot.  Which is a shame because like I said it has great reviews and some of the menue options look good. However, one bad experience is all it takes when you have unlimited choices.
Had awesome service at the bar

A rather posh feeling breakfest spot, but was super accomidating of families children. At brunch we spotted 4 families (including our own) with a little one. Loved the stickybun frenchtoast, as well as our savory dishes. A little on the pricy side, but service and food quality make it worth it.  2nd visit (3 star experience, 4star average). Service was atrocious. Failed to put in half of drink order for brunch, and 1st round took 10 min (while bartender was standing polishing glasses). Portions were even smaller than last time. Bread pudding was divine but only 6 small bites (for $13). Chilaquiles was mediocre. Egg dishes were fine, but not impressive. Waitress couldn't keep coffee full. And would have to be reminded over and over for a refill (both waters and coffee)... Unlikely to return at this point.

I'm struggling to understand premium pricing this place is charging. I ordered "The Kennison" burger, which tasted not too far from BigMac. A glass of wine had a good chunk of residue, which stuck in my teeth. The ambience was nothing special. Maybe, they charge for location? In any case, I'm not coming back.

I visited recently because I heard from some friends about the food.  The food is amazing, and it's only the second best part.  The service was absolutely phenomenal. We had a server Ben who knew everything about the menu and reccomending excellent dishes.  I hope management sees this because he provided one of the best dining experiences I've had in Chicago. Will be returning.
Good happy hour specials

It was absolutely amazing. I'm not a fine dine type of person but it was so amazing more then I had expected. Awesome and kind service. Fantastic food. I recommend this to anyone who is interested. On a scale of 1 to 10 it's over that's how amazing it is.
Nice ambiance, service, drinks, and food. Nice views of the park in a hotel setting.
Not alot of selection
We loved it. The service was great and friendly, and the food was delicious.

What a disappointment. The place was empty, nevertheless we were pressured to sit at a high top table and to order everything in one shot because "we have so many parties coming in, the chef doesn't want to make you wait for your food." So we did that. Then our water ran out and we were ignored by the staff. I got up and fetched my own water, it was the only thing to do. When they saw me do that, they hid from making eye contact. But then we were then OVER served, with every single person coming over interrupting us asking questions.  The food? Unimpressive. The burger was thin patties, nothing special. The chicken sandwich was uninspired. There were three different pasta options, all rather pretentious. We wound up ordering the one that was sold as, no kidding: "like walking through a forest on a fall day." It's made from lichens. This isn't an American classic, as this place advertises.  The cocktails were good. It's a shame our waiter didn't want to sell us more, but since we just wanted to get out of there, it's probably for the best.  $70 for bad service and blah food. Can't come back.
They've got great happy hour prices
Nice and comfortable place to hang on for brunch with roadside views.
Great food and attentive staff. We had the biscuits, cinnamon roll, chilaquiles, and burger. Good portions, well priced. The design of the space is lovely. Adding to our favorite neighborhood spots!
The most amazing Burgers and appetizers. Cold beer and great company.
Fantastic service.  Really attentive and especially with the grandkids
I had one of the best salads I've ever had here: peaches, burrata, lentils and sourdough. Outstanding
Food was fine; service was good.  Convenient if you're staying at the hotel.

On Wednesday they do a special of burger and a beer for $15. The burger was great! I ordered the pasta which was also delicious although pretty heavy even though I ordered the half portion.  It definitely doesn’t feel at all like a hotel restaurant.
The best!
Excellent food and service. Pricing is more than Google insinuated.
Nice  dog friendly patio. Friendly attentive staff.
Great food
Pretty overpriced for what you get
Tiny menu, with high prices for the portion.
Best pasta I've ever had, great menu in general, and excellent service!
The decor is very cool, kind of vintage upscale hotel. The food was good but not spectacular for the price. The bacon was incredible though. All in all an enjoyable experience.
We were impressed with the atmosphere.  Such a cool environment and the food was great!

We were really impressed with this place. Every dish and drink was really good! We especially loved the risotto starter and the pea and mint pasta. The gooey cake with sorbet was also amazing. Highly recommend checking this place out!

Had a brunch reservation at 11:30 for 2 but did not get seated until a little after noon. People with no reservations seem to have gotten seated before us so that was a bit aggravating. Got the Chilaquiles which was just okay. The cocktails however was on point. For dessert got the strawberry shortcake and the cake was a bit dry. The service was slow. I had to wait for sometime before I was able to get a coffee refill.  Overall I was excited to try this place but on this first visit it just fell flat in many areas.

I dined here last week and I’m still talking about it to people. The service was great, the food was phenomenal, the space is gorgeous, and the cocktails are perfect. I can’t wait to go back! I ended up going upstairs to the J. Parker to enjoy the view after dinner.

I live next door and stopped in for a mini-date. The service from Carlos was great and he was very knowledgeable about the menu. We had the Burrata and Short rib to start and split a Linguine and Clams. Sizeable portions for the starters. Everything was perfect and my lady loved it.

Delicious. Beautiful space. Solid wine and drink list. I had oysters, a salad and the halibut. All nicely done. The green almonds were a perfect seasonal touch. Attentive service. Great bar for dining solo or dining room/patio for date night.
The dining experience was ok. Great atmosphere and location. My pasta dish was very bland. It was hard to get the attention of service staff and they were not very helpful. The cocktails were great.
Amazing brunch and perfectly located for a nice walk in the park afterward. Loved it.
The staff is welcoming and very accommodating. Made us feel like we were their focus.
Boka always delivers
We're not vegetarians but had that awesome cauliflower steak it was too good. We also split the raviolis and they were easily the best Italian I've had all year. Definitely would come back.

An excellent neighbourhood spot offering excellent libations of classic American cocktails and contemporary variations.  The menu is varied in its ambitions as much as in its ingredients featuring something for the defter palate (Fish & Chips) as much as for the more refined one (Branzino) and offering real choice for the vegetarian.

Drinks, appetizer, and dessert were good enough. However, the salmon and trout entrees were disappointing. The salmon was smaller than expected and both dishes were dominated by the last expensive parts (lentils and frisee salad).  Good location, but if you're looking for a restaurant trying to compete on style and flavor, this might not be the right place.
Great food.  Grand experience.
Beautiful building. Loved the retro decorum. The food was very good and the portions just right. Price was reasonable for the quality of food. The service was very prompt and helpful.
Best new restaurant in Chicago.  Amazing drinks.  Terrific updated menu.  Fun takes on old classics.  I would give this place 6 stars if I could!!!
Another fantastic restaurant from the Boka group! I have eaten here twice and both times the food and service were phenomenal!
Excellent service, wonderful food, and with a killer aesthetic to boot, the Kennison was a fantastic dining experience. Their dishes are choice and their mix drink menu is a treat.

The food was extraordinarily fresh and delicious. The very talented young chef shops at the Farmer's Market across the street and invents his menus based on the ingredients, which shows. We had delicious happy hour oysters, prosecco, split a salad and for entrees, the salmon cooked a perfect medium rare, and a filet mignon that was also perfectly cooked to medium (can't digest medium rare anymore). The manager and chef comped us to a real treat, which was the pappardelle rabbit pasta, truly the best "dessert" we have ever had although not intended as a dessert. Mike our server was fantastic as well as John the asst mgr and Charles gave us great tips on hot spots in Chicago. We adored the friendly staff and spectacular food. While pricier than J Parker's rooftop bar atop the hotel, the food at Kennison's is more innovative and much higher quality.
Great cocktails, cool atmosphere, food is amazing, service is great, location is perfect.  Can't go wrong.

This is the 3rd time I've been to The Kennison and it gets better every single time. The service is always 5 star but this time we had Eric and he is one of the best waiters I've ever had. The food is always amazing but they recently added short ribs to the menu and it's outstanding. My dad pretty much gets short ribs every time he sees it on the menu and he said it's one of the best he's had. My mom tends to eat vegetarian dishes and got the Pastrami Carrots. Yes, carrots that actually smell and taste like pastrami!! They were unbelievable. Every time I've been here I get the string beans for the table and I suggest you do the same!! Can't say enough good things about this place.
Astounding service and seasonal good options.  This will be our "go to" spot for the area.
Popped in for a quick drink when I was just in Chicago. Great food, beer selection and ambiance. I highly recommend to check out - friendly service and everything else.
New place in the neighborhood. Of course it's overpriced.
Crab fritters (brown crab balls) did not impress. My cocktail helped redeem the place a bit but overall meh.

This new restaurant has very mediocre food and extremely small portion size. I ordered fish (bass) and it was mushy and flavorless. My husband and daughter ordered beef and pasta, and found the same lackluster experience in their entrees as well.  With so many other  better options in the old town Lincoln park area. I would pass on this restaurant.
Great experience at the bar. Lou and Emily are awesome. Loved the appetizers and cocktails. Look forward to going back!
